#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:3
msgid "Standalone Player"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:5
msgid ""
"The standalone player allows a Blender game to be run without having to load"
" the Blender system. This allows games to be distributed to other users, "
"without their requiring a detailed knowledge of Blender (and also without "
"the possibility of unauthorised modification). Note that the Game Engine "
"Save as Runtime is an addon facility which must be pre-loaded before use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:12
msgid ""
"The following procedure will give a standalone version of a working game."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:15
msgid ""
"**File - User Preferences - Addons: - Game Engine - Save as Game Engine "
"Runtime - Install Addon** (button)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:17
msgid ""
"(You can also **Save as Default** button, in which case the add-on will "
"always be present whenever Blender is re-loaded)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:20
msgid ""
"**File - Export - Save as Game Engine Runtime - (give appropriate "
"directory/filename)- Save as Game Engine Runtime** (button)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:22
msgid ""
"The game can then be executed by running the appropriate .exe file. Note "
"that all appropriate libraries are automatically loaded by the add-on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:25
msgid ""
"If you are interested in licensing your game, read `Licensing "
"<http://wiki.blender.org/index.php/User:sculptorjim/Game "
"Engine/Licensing>`__ for a discussion of the issues involved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:28
msgid "Exporting..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/blender_player.rst:30
msgid ""
"If the game is to be exported to other computers, make a new empty directory"
" for the game runtime and all its ancilliary libraries etc.  Then make sure "
"the **whole directory** is transferred to the target computer"
msgstr ""
